Tanzania's Chief of Defence Forces, General Venance Mabeyo has assured wananchi that the country’s borders are safe. General Mabeyo gave the assurance on Friday at requiem mass for President Magufuli held at Magufuli grounds in Chato, Geita. In the same development, Chief Mabeyo said all forces will obey the country’s new Commander-In-Chief of Armed Forces, President Samia Suhulu Hassan and assured her that she will get a deserved cooperation. "The Tanzania People's Defence Force wants to assure you that the country and its borders are safe and that they will continue to protect you as President and obey you as a commander-In-chief." said General Mabeyo.